On 12/14/2024 at 01:59 AM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/14/2024 at 06:55 AM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
Please be sure to send my packages over. I will never understand the person you became.
On 12/13/2024 at 08:19 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: Never)
Subject:Re: Adrian
Super frustrating not to be able to get answers to easy q’s. It’s a 30 second call but I wait hours. You know I’m going to respond because I have
milliseconds at best, but you do this anyway.
I finally got us on a call today and overcame weeks of bickering and crossed wires. It got the exact outcome you asked for, most in real time. So I
can’t understand why you don’t see that it works for you too.
Is working with me for the kids just beneath you?
On 12/13/2024 at 07:49 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: Never)
Subject:Re: Adrian
Is that what is arranged?
On 12/13/2024 at 07:39 PM, Christine Moyer wrote:
To:Robert Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:41 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
He should be fine for tomorrow at 9:15 pick up
On 12/13/2024 at 05:52 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:38 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
I’m getting worried because I don’t know how you plan to communicate or plan going into a Friday night again. Kari and Alan, and of course
AD and me don’t know if plans are changing tomorrow or not.
That puts me in an uncomfortable position to try and nudge you given past history and four people could be impacted. I don’t like being the
“nudger.” That is why I asked for two minutes on the phone.
This makes me feel uncomfortable.
On 12/13/2024 at 03:11 PM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/13/2024 at 07:40 PM)
Subject:Re: Adrian
I don’t know? Doesn’t he have Kari? Can we just talk for three minutes and I can let Alan know?
